@node INTRO " Introduction "

At the time of the #amiga97 IRC conference I took a look at Aminet to find
an AmIRC logfile stripper but didn't find any working ones.

So I decided to make my own and make it as good as possible.

@endnode

@node REQUI " Requirements "

LogConvert requires an Amiga computer with KS 2.0+ and a little free RAM.

@endnode

@node USAGE " Usage "

The program has to be run from CLI.

LogConvert [filename] [#channel] [slideshow] [simple] [complex] [columns n]

       filename: the filename of the input file
                 a ".LC" suffix will be added to the output filename

       #channel: which channel to convert

      slideshow: the lines will be printed to stdout with small delays
                 instead of writing them to an output file

         simple: convert only messages

        complex: convert everything - messages, joins, mode changes etc.

       colums n: wordwrap at n colums, where n>40

If you leave (some of) these command line options out, the program
will ask for them. The slideshow option makes an exception though.

You can break the program by pressing ctrl-c.

@endnode

